'''Patrik Schick''' (born 24 January 1996) is a Czech professional [[Football player|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

Born in Prague, Schick began his career with local club [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]], rising through their youth ranks, before making his senior debut as a teenager. He spent the 2015–16 season on loan with [[Bohemians 1905]], from where he moved at the age of 20 to [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in Italy. After his debut season in [[Serie A|Italy]], he moved to [[AS Roma|Roma]] in 2017. Having spent three years in Italy, Schick moved to Germany in 2019 to join [[RB Leipzig]] on a season-long loan before moving to Bayer Leverkusen on a permanent basis in September 2020. There he won a domestic [[Double (association football)|double]] of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] and the [[2023–24 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] in 2024.

Formerly an international at under-16, under-17, under-18, under-19, and under-21 levels, Schick made his senior debut for the Czech Republic in May 2016 at the age of 20. He has since helped the national team reach the quarter-finals of the [[UEFA European Championship|European Championship]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]], where he won both the Goal of the Tournament and the [[UEFA European Championship awards#Top goalscorer|Silver Boot]] awards as the joint-highest goalscorer of the tournament.

==Club career==
===Sparta Prague===
Schick was born in Prague and spotted by [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] when he was 11 years old.<ref name= Bundeprofile /> He made his top-flight debut for Sparta on 3 May 2014 in a 3–1 away loss at [[FK Teplice|Teplice]]. Sparta would win the domestic double that campaign but four appearances over two campaigns meant Schick crossed town to join [[Bohemians 1905]] on loan for the 2015–16 season.<ref name= Bundeprofile /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Bohemians získali útočníka, ze Sparty přichází na hostování Schick|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/fotbalista-patrik-schick-bude-ze-sparty-hostovat-v-bohemians-ptj-/fotbal.aspx?c=A150623_102828_fotbal_pes|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=23 June 2015|access-date=19 July 2017|language=cs}}</ref> He scored 8 goals in 27 outings for Bohemians during a relegation battle.<ref name=bleacher /><ref name=GUARD>{{cite web|title=Patrik Schick: the Czech Euros star who was told he would never make it|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/21/patrik-schick-czech-republic-euro-2020-star-england|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=21 July 2021|access-date=26 September 2021}}</ref> Schick returned to Sparta and was expected to feature prominently for the club during the 2016–17 season, but [[David Lafata]] was preferred and when Sparta offered Schick a new contract, his agent turned it down.<ref name=GUARD/>

===Sampdoria===
Schick signed for [[Serie A]] club [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in June 2016 for a reported fee of €4&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Schick nakonec Spartu opouští, podepsal smlouvu v Sampdorii Janov|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/patrik-schick-prestupuje-do-sampdorie-janov-fm5-/fotbal.aspx?c=A160713_193630_fotbal_tof|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=13 July 2016|access-date=19 July 2017|language=cs}}</ref> In his [[2016–17 Serie A|first season]] in Italy, he appeared in 32 league matches and scored 11 goals for Sampdoria.<ref name=bleacher /> He started 14 times and was able to score once every 137 minutes.<ref name=bleacher />

In May 2017, Schick refused to extend his contract, expecting a transfer to another club.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Fotbalový útočník Schick odmítl v Sampdorii nabídku nové smlouvy|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/patrik-schick-sampdoria-janov-smlouva-dhd-/fot_zahranici.aspx?c=A170512_111038_fot_zahranici_rou|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=12 May 2017|access-date=19 July 2017|language=cs}}</ref> In June 2017, [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] triggered the release clause of a reported €30 million on Schick's contract.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Schick absolvoval zdravotní prohlídku, už brzy přestoupí do Juventusu|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/fotbalista-patrik-schick-prestupuje-ze-sampdorie-janov-do-juventusu-123-/fot_zahranici.aspx?c=A170622_094646_fot_zahranici_pes|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=22 June 2017|access-date=19 July 2017|language=cs}}</ref> Schick failed two separate medicals and Juventus backed out of the deal on 18 July.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Schickův přestup se nekoná. Sampdoria se s Juventusem nedohodla|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/patrick-schick-sampdoria-juventus-prestup-fkf-/fot_zahranici.aspx?c=A170718_194653_fot_zahranici_ald|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=18 July 2017|access-date=19 July 2017|language=cs}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/official-club-statement-patrik-schick.php|title=Official club statement In relation to the player Patrik Schick|website=Juventus F.C.|date=18 July 2017|access-date=19 July 2017}}</ref>

===Roma===
On 29 August 2017, Schick joined [[AS Roma|Roma]] on loan for a fee of €5&nbsp;million with an option to buy for a further €9 million,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Patrik Schick signs for Roma in record deal|url=https://beta.asroma.com/en/news/41049/patrik-schick-signs-for-roma-in-record-deal|website=Beta AS Roma|date=14 July 2017}}</ref> once certain sporting objectives had been achieved, that could be rising up to a club record €40 million fee, which turn out to be unavailable.<ref name=GUARD /><ref>{{Cite news|title=Roma sign Patrik Schick from Sampdoria in club-record transfer|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/soccer-transfers/story/3191679/roma-sign-patrik-schick-from-sampdoria-in-club-record-transfer|website=ESPN|date=29 August 2017|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref> Upon signing, Roma sporting director [[Monchi]] described Schick as "one of the brightest prospects in international football."<ref name=ATHL>{{cite web|title=Patrik Schick strikes from 50 yards as he hits two goals against Scotland|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4210433/2021/06/07/patrik-schick-strikes-from-50-yards-as-he-hits-two-goals-against-scotland/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=14 June 2021}}</ref> Schick spent most of his spell at Roma playing out on the right wing or left up front by himself, and he scored only eight times in 58 games.<ref name=ATHL />

====2019–20: Loan to RB Leipzig====
On 2 September 2019, [[Bundesliga]] club [[RB Leipzig]] announced the signing of Schick on a season-long loan deal with an option to buy him permanently.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Transfermeldung: Patrik Schick kommt Leihweise zu RB Leipzig|url=https://www.dierotenbullen.com/de/aktuelles/neuigkeiten/Saison_2019_20/Neuzugang-Patrik-Schick.html|website=RB Leipzig|date=2 September 2019|access-date=2 September 2019|language=de|archive-date=25 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625131109/https://www.dierotenbullen.com/de/aktuelles/neuigkeiten/Saison_2019_20/Neuzugang-Patrik-Schick.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> His first goal for Leipzig came in a 3–2 defeat of [[SC Paderborn 07|SC Paderborn]] on 11 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/paderborn-rb-leipzig-live-line-ups-stats-timo-werner-nagelsmann-sabitzer-adams-8392|title=Timo Werner strikes again as RB Leipzig hold on for win against spirited Paderborn|website=Bundesliga|date=11 November 2019|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref> This started a run of three goals in four league appearances including coming off the bench to complete the comeback and secure a 3–3 draw with [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref name=Bundeprofile/><ref>{{Cite news|title=Dortmund's Jadon Sancho scores again in 3-3 thriller with leaders RB Leipzig|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/dec/17/jadon-sancho-borussia-dortmund-rb-leipzig-bundesliga-roundup|website=The Guardian|date=17 December 2019|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref> Alongside [[Timo Werner]], Schick rekindled his form with 10 goals in 28 games for Leipzig as the club finished in third place in the [[2019–20 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] and reached the semi-finals of the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref name=ATHL/><ref>{{Cite news|title=Paris St-Germain are through to their first Champions League final courtesy of a deserved victory over RB Leipzig in an entertaining semi-final in Lisbon.|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/53759778|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=18 August 2020|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
====2020–21: Debut season====
On 8 September 2020, Schick joined [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on a five-year contract for a reported fee of €26.5 million plus bonuses, getting the number 14 on his jersey.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Patrik Schick seals move to Bayer 04|url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/patrik-schick-seals-move-to-bayer-04|website=Bayer Leverkusen|date=8 September 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Schick joins Bayer Leverkusen|url=https://beta.asroma.com/en/news/58762/schick-joins-bayer-leverkusen|website=AS Roma|date=8 September 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Bayer Leverkusen verstärkt sich mit Patrik Schick|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/patrik-schick-bayer-leverkusen-transfer-rb-leipzig-as-rom-sturmer-wechsel-2025-12757|website=Bundesliga|date=8 September 2020|language=de}}</ref>

Schick scored his first goal in a [[UEFA#Competitions|UEFA competition]] on 26 November 2020, coming in a 4–1 victory over Israeli club [[Hapoel Be'er Sheva F.C.|Hapoel Be'er Sheva]] in the group stage of the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Leverkusen 4–1 H. Beer-Sheva|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029782--leverkusen-vs-h-beer-sheva/|website=[[UEFA]]|date=26 November 2020|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref> On 19 December 2020, Schick scored a volley against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in a 2–1 loss for Leverkusen.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Schick's powerful volley puts Leverkusen in front|url=https://www.espn.com.sg/video/clip/_/id/30554292|work=[[ESPN]]|date=19 December 2020|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=19 December 2020|title=Lewandowski shows Bayer Leverkusen why he's The Best|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/bayer-leverkusen-vs-bayern-munich/cronica/2020/12/19/5fde5ece46163f6a698b45d8.html|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|access-date=27 February 2025}}</ref> He was the preferred centre-forward for much of the [[2020–21 Bayer 04 Leverkusen season|2020–21 campaign]] at the [[BayArena]] and finished with nine strikes across 29 league games.<ref name=Bundeprofile>{{cite web|title=Patrik Schick: Who is Bayer Leverkusen's free-scoring Czech forward?|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-patrik-schick-bayer-leverkusen-czech-republic-forward-8833|website=Bundesliga|date=14 June 2021|archive-date=14 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210614231237/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-patrik-schick-bayer-leverkusen-czech-republic-forward-8833}}</ref>

====2021–22: Record breaking season====
On 4 October 2021, Schick scored his first brace for Leverkusen and provided an assist against [[Arminia Bielefeld]] which ended a 4-0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Patrik Schick double as Bayer Leverkusen ease past Arminia Bielefeld |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/arminia-bielefeld-bayer-leverkusen-live-line-ups-stats-schick-wirtz-frimpong-17475|website=Bundesliga|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> Schick continued his goalscoring threat scoring once in the next two league games against [[1. FC Köln]] and [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] before he tore his ankle ligament.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beňo |first=David|title=Bad news for Schick, he injured ligaments in his ankle. He probably won't go to the national team, how long will he be out? |url=https://ruiksport.com/bad-news-for-schick-he-injured-ligaments-in-his-ankle-he-probably-wont-go-to-the-national-team-how-long-will-he-be-out/|website=RuikSport|date=25 October 2021|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=#KOEB04 review: Schick equals club record|url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bundesliga/koeb04-review-schick-equals-club-record |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen|publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen Fussball GmbH}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayern 5-1 Leverkusen|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/608608/bayern-munich-bayer-leverkusen|website=ESPN UK|publisher=ESPN|date=17 October 2021|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> On 4 December 2021, Schick scored four goals and provided an assist – all in the second half – in a 7–1 victory against [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]], which is the most goals in a single game from an individual in Leverkusen's history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Four-goal Schick leads Leverkusen to 7-1 demolition of Fuerth|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/608664|website=[[ESPN]]|date=4 December 2021|access-date=4 December 2021}}</ref> He continued his good form in Leverkusen's next two league games, scoring a [[Hat-trick#Association football|brace]] in each match against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] (not only a brace but also the 5000th penalty scored in the Bundesliga's history),<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 December 2021 |title=5000 and 1000: Schick's very special penalty in Frankfurt |url=https://www.sportsoftheday.com/5000-and-1000-schicks-very-special-penalty-in-frankfurt/ |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=Sports of the Day}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Eintracht Frankfurt 5:2 Bayer 04 Leverkusen|url=https://www.dfb.de/bundesliga/spieltagtabelle/?spieledb_path=%2Fdatencenter%2Fbundesliga%2F2021-22%2F15-spieltag%2Feintracht-frankfurt-bayer-04-leverkusen-2327021|website=[[German Football Association]]|date=12 December 2021|access-date=15 December 2021|language=de}}</ref> and [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2:2 gegen Hoffenheim – Remis im letzten Heimspiel des Jahres|url=https://www.bayer04.de/de-de/news/bundesliga/2-2-gegen-hoffenheim-remis-im-letzten-heimspiel-des-jahres|website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen|date=15 December 2021|language=de}}</ref> Because of this, Schick won Bundesliga Player of the month by scoring eight goals and one assist in the four matches he played.<ref>{{Cite web |title="Patrik Schick is in the same category as Robert Lewandowski and Erling Haaland" - Rudi Völler |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/patrik-schick-in-the-same-category-as-lewandowski-and-haaland-leverkusen-18673 |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=Bundesliga}}</ref> In the first half of the season, Schick scored 16 goals in 14 games, while also missing a few games due to injury, and was only behind [[Robert Lewandowski]] in the top goalscoring charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/analysis/bundesliga-202122-patrik-schick-bayer-leverkusen-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics|title=Patrick Schick: How the Bayer Leverkusen striker has started the season in red-hot form – scout report|first=David|last=Seymour|work=Total Football Analysis|date=23 September 2021|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref>

Following the mid-season winter break, Schick scored four times in six league matches. In the sixth game against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] he scored from a long range shot outside the box, but in the 49th minute of the same game, he tore his muscle fibre in the calf region, causing him to miss the following six games.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 February 2022 |title=Leverkusen top-scorer Patrik Schick out with calf injury |url=https://apnews.com/article/soccer-sports-bundesliga-bayer-leverkusen-f059283dbf841513f3cefe69f2adc538|website=Associated Press|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> He scored four goals and provided two assists in the last four matchdays of the [[2021–22 Bundesliga|2021–22 season]], most notably a double against Hoffenheim, which secured his club's place for Champions League for the following season, and just missing out on the goalscoring record held by [[Stefan Kießling]] by a single goal. He ended the season as the league's second highest scorer with 24 goals in 27 matches, while winning Leverkusen's player of the season award,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Player of the Season 2021/22: Patrik Schick is number one {{!}} Bayer04.de |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/player-of-the-season-202122-patrik-schick-is-number-one|website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen|publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen Fussball GmbH|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> then extended his contract with the club until 2027.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/world-class-striker-patrik-schick-signs-new-deal |title=World class striker Patrik Schick signs new deal |website=Bayer Leverkusen |date=26 May 2022}}</ref>

====2022–23: Injury crisis====
On 3 September 2022, Schick scored his first goal of the season against [[SC Freiburg|Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/bundesliga/2022-2023/sc-freiburg-2-3-bayer-leverkusen-xabi-alonsos-side-restore-10-point-advantage-over-bayern-munich-wit_sto10062699/story.shtml|title=SC Freiburg 2-3 Bayer Leverkusen {{!}} Xabi Alonso's Side Restore 10-point Advantage Over Bayern Munich with Win|website=Eurosport|first=Desmond|last=Kane|date=17 March 2024|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref> On 7 September, in the [[2022-23 UEFA Champions League]] match against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], Schick scored a header which was controversially ruled out from [[Video assistant referee|VAR]], ten minutes after Schick scored a bicycle kick which was ruled out for offside.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Club Brugge 1-0 Leverkusen Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/652598|website=ESPN|date=7 September 2022|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> Schick made it back to back games scoring and this time was against [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Honours even as Hertha Berlin and Bayer Leverkusen produce second-half fireworks |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/hertha-berlin-bayer-leverkusen-live-team-news-match-stats-hudson-odoi-azmoun-21200 |access-date=22 May 2024|website=Bundesliga}}</ref> Schick received an adductor injury.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Leverkusen striker Schick out for 'weeks' with calf injury |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/leverkusen-striker-schick-out-for-weeks-with-calf-injury-20220220-CMS-371993.html|website=World Soccer Talk|date=21 February 2022|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> On 19 February 2023 he scored immediately off the bench after being out for several weeks against Mainz.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mainz 3-2 Leverkusen Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/638618/mainz-bayer-leverkusen|website=ESPN|date=19 February 2023|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> He again was involved in a goal and provided an assist in a 4-1 victory against Hertha Berlin.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer 04 Leverkusen - Hertha BSC {{!}} Season 2022/2023|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/matchday/2022-2023/23/bayer-04-leverkusen-vs-hertha-bsc/liveticker |access-date=22 May 2024|website=Bundesliga}}</ref> Schick got an adductor injury again, which meant he would miss the rest of the season and the first half of the next season, overall missing 34 matches due to injury in this season.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-bestaetigt-operation-schick-faellt-noch-mehrere-monate-aus-958859/artikel |title=Leverkusen bestätigt Operation: Schick fällt noch mehrere Monate aus|magazine=Kicker|publisher=Olympia-Vertlag GmbH|language=de |date=11 July 2023 }}</ref>

====2023–24: Comeback and historic success====
On 30 November 2023, Schick returned from a long-time injury with a goal in a 2–0 away victory against [[BK Häcken]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|2023–24 Europa League]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/hacken-vs-leverkusen/spielbericht/499041 |title=Boniface & Schick treffen: Bayer macht Gruppensieg klar|website=[[Sky Sport (Germany)|Sky Sport Germany]]|publisher=Sky Group|language=de |date=30 November 2023 }}</ref> then went on to score five more goals and provide one assist in six more matches in all competitions. On 3 December, he came on as a substitute in the 79th minute and went on to assist a vital goal in the same minute to [[Victor Boniface]] against Borussia Dortmund to extend Leverkusen's unbeaten streak.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/2023/12/bundesliga-bayer-leverkusen-bvb-11-boniface-rettet-bayers-serie |title=Super-Joker rettet Bayer im Topspiel|website=Sport1|publisher=Sport1 Medien AG|language=de|date=3 December 2023 }}</ref> On 20 December, he scored a first-half hat-trick against [[VfL Bochum]], with the game finishing in a 4–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/de-de/news/bundesliga/4-0-gegen-bochum-gelungener-jahresabschluss-mit-schick-hattrick |title=4:0 gegen Bochum – Gelungener Jahresabschluss mit Schick-Hattrick|website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen|publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen Fussball GmbH|language=de |date=21 December 2023 }}</ref>

In March 2024, Schick scored three critical goals to keep Bayer Leverkusen in the Europa League in their round of 16 tie against [[Qarabağ FK]]. During the first leg in [[Baku]], he scored the equalizing stoppage-time goal for Leverkusen, ending in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Harry|last=Sherlock|title=Relief for Xabi Alonso! Harry Kane's Bundesliga rivals Bayer Leverkusen preserve unbeaten record with 92nd-minute equaliser in stunning finish to Europa League clash at Qarabag|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/xabi-alonso-harry-kane-bundesliga-bayern-munich-bayer-leverkusen/blt26c28d9f0ef358c5#cs0a94f6653783e7cc|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=7 March 2024|access-date=14 March 2024}}</ref> In the following leg, he scored two stoppage-time goals to end the game in a 3–2 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Peter|last=McVitie|title=Xabi Alonso is immortal! Harry Kane's title rivals Bayer Leverkusen score two stoppage time goals to defeat Qarabag, reaching Europa League quarter-finals & preserving incredible 37-game unbeaten run|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/xabi-alonso-harry-kane-bayer-leverkusen-goals-qarabag-europa-league-quarter-finals-unbeaten/bltbbc448b1cb72ecef|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=14 March 2024}}</ref> On 30 March, he scored a stoppage-time winner in a 2–1 victory over Hoffenheim, which secured his club's qualification for the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|UEFA Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/bayer-04-leverkusen-tsg-1899-hoffenheim-27-spieltag-spielbericht-26796 |title=Last-Minute-Doppelschlag lässt Bayer 04 Leverkusen jubeln!|website=Bundesliga|date=30 March 2024|language=de}}</ref> On 5 May, against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], Schick scored a header in a 5–1 victory for Leverkusen to extend their 48-game unbeaten streak.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer Leverkusen equal Benfica's European record with Eintracht Frankfurt win |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/eintracht-frankfurt-bayer-leverkusen-free-highlights-roma-preview-report-alonso-invincibles-27166 |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website |language=en}}</ref> On 12 May, against VfL Bochum, Schick scored the opening goal of a 5–0 Leverkusen win, making history as the club's 50th game unbeaten.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leverkusen 5–0 Bochum (May 12, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/677879/bayer-leverkusen-vfl-bochum|website=ESPN|date=12 May 2024|access-date=22 May 2024}}</ref> On 18 May 2024, in the final day of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|season]] Schick was a part of the first ever unbeaten Bundesliga season with Bayer Leverkusen.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Omar|last=Garrick|title=Leverkusen become first team to go unbeaten in Bundesliga |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5503124/2024/05/18/bayer-leverkusen-undefeated-bundesliga/|newspaper=The New York Times|date=18 May 2024|access-date=22 May 2024|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In the [[2024 DFB-Pokal final|DFB-Pokal final]] Schick helped his team win 1–0 against [[1. FC Kaiserslautern|Kaiserslautern]], to make it a special double trophy winning season, then he prepared for the upcoming [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]] tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Stafford-Bloor |first=Sebastian |title=Leverkusen win DFB-Pokal to end dream domestic season unbeaten. Now they can celebrate |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5519158/2024/05/26/leverkusen-win-dfb-pokal-unbeaten/ |access-date=13 June 2024|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=26 May 2024 |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=28 May 2024|title=Schick heads Leverkusen trio in Czech Euro 2024 squad |url=https://www.thecourier.com.au/story/8644572/schick-heads-leverkusen-trio-in-czech-euro-2024-squad/|newspaper=[[The Courier (Ballarat)|The Courier Ballarat]]|access-date=13 June 2024}}</ref>

====2024–25: Defending champions====
In the [[2024 DFL-Supercup]] at the start of the season against [[VfB Stuttgart]], Schick scored an equaliser in the 88th minute to make the score 2–2 and bring on a penalty shoot-out, during which he scored and Leverkusen won 4–3 to win their first ever Supercup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj627k1j4j3t|title=German Super Cup: Bayer Leverkusen beat Stuttgart on penalties after late Patrik Schick goal|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=17 August 2024|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref> On 23 November, Schick scored a hat-trick against [[1. FC Heidenheim|Heidenheim]] in a 5–2 comeback victory.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bundesliga 2024–25: Bayer Leverkusen's Patrik Schick scores hat-trick in comeback win over Heidenheim|url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/bundesliga/bayer-leverkusen-vs-heidenheim-score-results-bundesliga-2024-25-patrik-schick-hattrick-goals-highlights-football-news/article68904713.ece|website=sportstar.thehindu.com|date=24 November 2024|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref> Three days later, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 5–0 victory over [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-red-bull-salzburg-live-champions-league-blog-preview-report-29764 |title=Bayer Leverkusen ease past Red Bull Salzburg with emphatic UEFA Champions League win |publisher=Bundesliga |date=27 November 2024 }}</ref> On Schick's 100th league appearance in a match against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]] on 30 November, Schick scored in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ryan|last=Fisher|title=Leverkusen move up to third in Bundesliga after Schick nets winner against Union Berlin|url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/union-berlin-bayer-leverkusen-report-2024-11-30/082Fn2io/|website=Flash Score|date=30 November 2024|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref> On 21 December, Schick scored four goals in a 5–1 win over Freiburg, surpassing [[Jan Koller]]'s 61 goal record for Czech players in the league.<ref>{{Cite news |date=21 December 2024 |title=Super Schick nets four as Leverkusen thrash Freiburg 5-1 |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/schick-nets-four-leverkusen-thrash-freiburg-5-1-2024-12-21/ |access-date=21 December 2024 |work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/top-scorers-nations-harry-kane-schick-lewandowski-muller-robben-30328 |title=Who are the Bundesliga's top scorers from each country? |publisher=Bundesliga |date=10 January 2025 }}</ref> On 5 February 2025, he netted a brace, including a stoppage-time equalizer, against 1. FC Köln in the [[2024–25 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] quarter-final, which ended in a 3–2 victory after extra time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/de-de/news/dfb-pokal/3-2-gegen-koeln-werkself-nach-derbysieg-im-halbfinale |title=3:2 gegen Köln – Werkself nach Derbysieg im Halbfinale |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |language=de |date=5 February 2025 }}</ref> Schick ended the 2024–25 season as top goal scorer for Leverkusen across all competitions with 27 goals and behind only [[Harry Kane]] as the top-scorer in the league.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.topscorersfootball.com/bundesliga | title=Top scorers Bundesliga, Germany 2024/2025 }}</ref>

====2025–26====
On 4 August 2025, Schick extended his contract with Leverkusen until 2030.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/patrik-schick-signs-contract-extension-at-bayer-leverkusen-35164869|title=Patrik Schick signs contract extension at Bayer Leverkusen|date=18 February 2026|website=OneFootball}}</ref> On 15 August, in a DFB-Pokal match against [[SG Sonnenhof Großaspach|Großaspach]], Schick scored Leverkusen’s first goal under [[Erik ten Hag]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/soccer/ten-hag-makes-successful-debut-after-bayer-leverkusen-wins-4-0-in-german-cup/ar-AA1KBk8R?ocid=BingNewsSerp|title=MSN|website=www.msn.com}}</ref>
On 30 August, Schick scored a brace in a 3–3 draw against [[Werder Bremen]] which concluded Ten Hag's era at Leverkusen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/werder-bremen-bayer-leverkusen-match-report-highlights-matchday-2-33759|title=Werder Bremen stun Bayer Leverkusen with unlikeliest of comebacks|website=www.bundesliga.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cd7y19095rno|title=Erik ten Hag sacked: Bayer Leverkusen fire ex-Man Utd boss after two league games|date=1 September 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> Schick continued his good form and scored a penalty against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in [[Kasper Hjulmand]]'s first game to earn Leverkusen their first Bundesliga win of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/video/clip/_/id/46235925|title=Patrik Schick scores penalty goal vs. Eintracht Frankfurt - ESPN Video|website=ESPN}}</ref> On 14 March 2026, he featured in his 200th match for Leverkusen in a 1–1 draw with Bayern Munich.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-asia/football/bundesliga/articles/bayer-leverkusen-1-1-bayern-munich-jackson-diaz-see-red-as-leaders-hold-on-for-draw-2026-03-14 |title=Bayer Leverkusen 1-1 Bayern Munich: Jackson, Diaz see red as leaders hold on for draw |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=14 March 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/zahlen-des-spieltags-rekorde-jubilaen-serie-26-spieltags-36443 |title=Undavs Super-Serie, Olises Assist-Rekord |publisher=Bundesliga |language=de |date=15 March 2026 }}</ref> On 25 April, he scored his 100th goal for Leverkusen in all competitions, in a 2–1 victory over [[FC Cologne|Cologne]], in the ''Rheinisches Derby''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Cologne 1-2 Leverkusen (25 Apr, 2026) Final Score - ESPN (AU) |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/match/_/gameId/746989/bayer-leverkusen-fc-cologne |access-date=2026-04-28 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Patrik Schick 20180601 AUSCZE 3910 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Schick with the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] in 2018]]
Schick was called up to the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] senior side for the first time at their pre-[[UEFA Euro 2016]] training camp.<ref name=bleacher>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2737686-patrik-schick-has-world-at-his-feet-but-the-time-has-come-to-deliver-on-promise|first=Adam|last=Digby|title=Patrik Schick Has World at His Feet, but the Time Has Come to Deliver on Promise|website=Bleacher Report|date=3 June 2018|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref> He made his national team debut in a friendly match against [[Malta national football team|Malta]] on 27 May 2016, scoring after coming on as a second-half substitute in a 6–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Miloslav|last=Novák|title=Česko 6–0 Malta: Pohodový test. Rosický hrál, Čech má rekord|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2016/cesko-malta-priprava-na-euro.A160527_094419_euro-2016_elv|newspaper=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=27 May 2016|access-date=24 June 2021}}</ref>

===UEFA Euro 2020===
On 25 May 2021, Schick was included in the Czech Republic's final 26-man squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020]] tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=Česká reprezentace oznámila nominaci na UEFA Euro 2020|trans-title=The Czech national team announced the squad for UEFA Euro 2020|url=https://repre.fotbal.cz/ceska-reprezentace-oznamila-nominaci-na-uefa-euro-2020/a14226|publisher=[[Football Association of the Czech Republic]]|date=25 May 2021|access-date=25 May 2021|language=cs}}</ref> In the first group stage match against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] on 14 June at [[Hampden Park]] in [[Glasgow]], Schick scored both goals as the Czech Republic won 2–0.<ref name=CzeSco>{{cite web|first=Charles|last=Paterson|title=Scotland 0–2 Czech Republic: Patrik Schick double sees off Scots at Euro 2020|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/scotland-vs-czech-republic/report/421491|website=Sky Sports|date=14 June 2021}}</ref> The second strike from the halfway line was the longest-recorded goal at the Euros since 1980 at {{convert|45|metres|yards}}. The goal was later voted as the "goal of the tournament",<ref name="goaleuro"/><ref name=CzeSco /><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2021/06/14/patrik-schick-goal-video-czech-republic-scotland-euros|first=Andrew|last=Gastelum|title=Czech Republic's Schick Scores From Halfway Line, Longest Goal at Euros Since 1980|magazine=Sports Illustrated|date=14 June 2021}}</ref> and was nominated for the [[FIFA Puskás Award]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Adithya|last=Namboothiri|title=Patrik Schick scores a stunner as Czechs defeat Scots 2–0|url=https://footballexpress.co.uk/patrik-schick-scores-a-stunner-as-czechs-defeat-scots-2-0/|url-status=dead|website=Football Express|date=16 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128123016/https://footballexpress.co.uk/patrik-schick-scores-a-stunner-as-czechs-defeat-scots-2-0/|archive-date=28 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=FIFA Puskás Award: 11 best goals announced|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/media-releases/the-best-2021-fifa-puskas-award-11-announced|website=FIFA|date=30 November 2021}}</ref> He became the first Czech footballer since [[Tomáš Rosický]] at the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] to score a brace at a major tournament and [[Milan Baroš]] in [[UEFA Euro 2004|2004]] to do so at the European Championship.<ref name=CzeSco/><ref>{{cite web|first=Danny|last=Lewis|title=Czech Republic 3–0 Denmark at Euro 2004: The Dark Heroes who blazed a path to the final|url=https://thesefootballtimes.co/2020/06/27/czech-republic-3-0-denmark-at-euro-2004-the-dark-horses-who-blazed-a-path-to-the-final/|website=These Football Times|date=27 June 2020|access-date=14 June 2021}}</ref>

Against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] on 18 June, Schick scored from a penalty to help his nation earn a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Croatia-Czech Republic UEFA Euro 2020|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024462--croatia-vs-czech-republic/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317165037/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024462--croatia-vs-czech-republic/|url-status=dead|archive-date=17 March 2020|website=UEFA|date=18 June 2021|access-date=3 July 2021}}</ref> On 27 June, he scored his fourth goal of the tournament in the Czech Republic's victory over the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ryan|last=Sidle|title=Czech Republic shock Netherlands to get into Euro 2020 Quarter Finals|url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-netherlands-lost-2-0-to-czech-republic-in-euro-2020-last-16-game-20210627|website=Sport Bible|date=27 June 2021|access-date=27 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627175702/https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-netherlands-lost-2-0-to-czech-republic-in-euro-2020-last-16-game-20210627|archive-date=27 June 2021|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 3 July, he scored in a 2–1 controversial defeat against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] in the quarter-finals to equal Milan Baroš' record of five goals for the Czech Republic in a European Championship tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Schick in sight of Baroš record|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/news/026b-12a72f1f34e5-e39d32c5f271-1000--schick-in-sight-of-baros-record/|website=UEFA|date=3 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210703123616/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/news/026b-12a72f1f34e5-e39d32c5f271-1000--schick-in-sight-of-baros-record/|archive-date=3 July 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Jonathan|last=Johnson|title=Czech Republic vs. Denmark score: Two early goals put Danes through to UEFA Euro 2020 semifinals|url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/czech-republic-vs-denmark-score-two-early-goals-put-danes-through-to-uefa-euro-2020-semifinals/|website=[[CBS Sports]]|date=3 July 2021}}</ref> Alongside [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], he was the [[UEFA Euro 2020]] joint top scorer with five goals, with the higher number of goals scored from open play.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Dan|last=Bernstein|title=Ronaldo wins Euro 2020 Golden Boot on tie-breaker over Schick|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/ronaldo-wins-euro-2020-golden-boot-on-tie-breaker-over/wzri2apw8gef1bnfwv1uauvhf|website=Goal|date=11 July 2021|access-date=12 July 2021}}</ref>

===2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying===
In the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|2022 World Cup Qualifiers]] against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]], Schick scored and provided [[Adam Hlozek|Hlozek]]'s first goal for the national team, and it ended a comfortable 2–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dupare |first=Shubham |date=10 October 2021|title=Belarus vs Czech Republic prediction, preview, team news and more {{!}} 2022 FIFA World Cup Qualifiers |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/belarus-vs-czech-republic-prediction-preview-team-news-2022-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers|website=Sportskeeda|access-date=7 December 2024}}</ref> He was injured for the remaining fixtures and the Czechs failed to qualify.<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 November 2021|title=World Cup 2022: Czech Republic Gets Second Chance in Playoffs |url=https://praguemorning.cz/world-cup-2022-czech-republic-gets-second-chance/ |access-date=13 June 2024|website=Prague Morning}}</ref> On 27 September 2022, in a match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A|Nations League]], Schick scored a goal after being injured for many months and sidelined away from the national team for almost one year, but the Czechs lost 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/uefa-nations-league/2022-2023/switzerland-v-czech-republic-nations-league-live_sto9162296/story.shtml|first=Alex|last=Smith|title=Switzerland 2–1 Czech Republic: Strikes from Remu Freuler and Breel Embolo Keep Swiss in Nations League Elite|website=Eurosport|date=27 September 2022|access-date=6 December 2024}}</ref>

===UEFA Euro 2024===
On 29 May 2024, Schick was included in the final Czech squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|first1=Ryan|last1=Dabbs|first2=Tom|last2=Hancock|first3=Karel|last3=Haring|title=Czech Republic Euro 2024 squad: Ivan Hašek's full team|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/czech-republic-euro-2024-squad-team-players-line-up-germany|magazine=[[FourFourTwo]]|date=26 June 2024|access-date=19 May 2025}}</ref> On 10 June, the nation's final pre-tournament match against [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]], Schick had a goal ruled offside,<ref>{{Cite news |date=11 June 2024|title=Czechs beat North Macedonia 2-1 in their final Euro 2024 warm-up |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/czechs-beat-north-macedonia-2-1-in-their-final-euro-2024-warm-up|newspaper=[[The Straits Times]]|access-date=13 June 2024|issn=0585-3923}}</ref> but went on to score from the penalty spot in a 2–1 victory for the Czechs.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Friendlies: Czech Republic 2–1 North Macedonia|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cd11w404469t|website=BBC Sport|date=10 June 2024|access-date=13 June 2024}}</ref> In the tournament, he scored the equaliser against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in a 1–1 group stage draw, which was also his 20th goal for the national team,<ref>{{Cite news|first=Henry|last=Clark|title=Georgia 1–1 Czechia: Patrik Schick scores equaliser from close range after Georges Mikautadze opened the scoring with a penalty as both sides are left waiting for their first win at Euro 2024|url=https://www.msn.com/en-au/sport/football/georgia-1-1-czechia-patrik-schick-scores-equaliser-from-close-range-after-georges-mikautadze-opened-the-scoring-with-a-penalty-as-both-sides-are-left-waiting-for-their-first-win-at-euro-2024/ar-BB1oHrkO|website=[[MSN]]|date=22 June 2024|access-date=24 July 2024}}</ref> only to suffer from a calf injury ten minutes later.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Schick saves Czechs in Euros draw against gutsy Georgia|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/other/schick-saves-czechs-in-euros-draw-against-gutsy-georgia/ar-BB1oHCA8|website=[[MSNBC]]|date=22 June 2024|access-date=24 July 2024|archive-date=10 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241210191956/https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/other/schick-saves-czechs-in-euros-draw-against-gutsy-georgia/ar-BB1oHCA8|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===2026 FIFA World Cup qualifying===
On 22 March 2025, Schick scored both of his nation's goals against [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] in a 2–1 victory to start the Czech Republic's campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.ceskatelevize.cz/clanek/fotbal/schick-to-zaridil-fotbaliste-na-uvod-kvalifikace-ms-udolali-faerske-ostrovy/67ded41d3128e7e935e0e324|title=Sestřih: Schick to zařídil. Fotbalisté na úvod kvalifikace MS udolali Faerské ostrovy|language=cs|website=[[ČT Sport]]|publisher=[[Czech Television]]|date=22 March 2025|access-date=19 May 2025}}</ref> On 25 March, he scored once against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] in a 4–0 victory. By doing so, he became the top scorer at that point in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] with three goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/0297-1d5d6735f8d7-9bf819c5c8e9-1000--european-qualifiers-top-scorer-patrik-schick-on-top/|title=European Qualifiers top scorer: Patrik Schick on top|website=UEFA|date=25 March 2025|access-date=19 May 2025}}</ref> The Czech Republic eventually finished second in Group L behind Croatia, qualifying for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|play-offs]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/czechs-ease-6-0-win-over-gibraltar-world-cup-qualifier-2025-11-17/ |title=Czechs ease to 6-0 win over Gibraltar in World Cup qualifier |publisher=Reuters |date=17 November 2025 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Although Schick mostly plays in a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|central role]] as a main [[Striker (association football)|striker]], he is also capable of playing as a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]] or as a right [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]].<ref name="centravanti">{{Cite news|first=Stefano|last=Chioffi|title=Schick, il centravanti della Repubblica Ceca Under 21 è entrato nei piani di mezza Serie A|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/talent-scout/2016/06/14-12468293/schick_il_centravanti_della_repubblica_ceca_under_21_e_entrato_nei_piani_di_mezza_serie_a/|website=[[Corriere dello Sport]]|date=14 June 2016|access-date=12 March 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref name="Schick sceglie la Samp">{{Cite news|title=Schick sceglie la Samp, Dodò a un passo |publisher=La Repubblica|url=https://genova.repubblica.it/sport/2016/07/09/news/schick_sceglie_la_samp_dodo_a_un_passo-143740542/|website=[[La Repubblica]]|date=9 July 2016|access-date=12 March 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref name="2ndSeason">{{Cite news|first=Damien|last=Hawkes|title=Patrik Schick Hoping for 2nd Season Success|url=https://www.praguepost.com/sports/patrik-schick-hoping-for-2nd-season-success|website=[[Prague Post]]|date=17 June 2018|access-date=12 March 2019}}</ref> He can hold up the ball with his back to goal, but is also an agile player, who possesses technique and [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, which enables him to play the ball first time, participate in the build-up of attacking plays and provide [[Assist (football)|assists]].<ref name="centravanti"/><ref name="2ndSeason"/> Schick is also known for his signature celebration: every time he scores a goal, he flexes his muscles in front of the fans.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 June 2021 |title=Schick says goal celebration a tribute to MMA fighter |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/schick-says-goal-celebration-a-tribute-to-mma-fighter-20210619-CMS-337614.html |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=World Soccer Talk |language=en}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Schick has an older sister, Kristýna Schicková (born 31 July 1994), who is a model and a social media influencer.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Kristyna Schickova - Models|url=https://www.eastwestmodels.de/women/2226-kristyna-schickova/|url-status=dead|website=East West Models|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230424014011/https://www.eastwestmodels.de/women/2226-kristyna-schickova/|archive-date=24 April 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Fast confession - model Kristýna Schicková: She charmed Jon Bon Jovi or Leonardo DiCaprio|url=https://www.lp-life.com/fast-confession-model-kristyna-schickova-she-charmed-jon-bon-jovi-or-leonardo-dicaprio|website=Luxury Prague Life|date=13 September 2020|access-date=13 September 2021|archive-date=7 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230607224939/https://www.lp-life.com/fast-confession-model-kristyna-schickova-she-charmed-jon-bon-jovi-or-leonardo-dicaprio|url-status=dead}}</ref> In his teenage years, Schick considered a career as a model but focused on competitive football instead. Growing up, his footballing hero was [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] player [[Wayne Rooney]].<ref name=GUARD />

In July 2020, Schick married his long-time girlfriend Hana Běhounková (born 1996). They have two children named Victoria and Nico, born in October 2020 and 2021 respectively.<ref>{{cite web|title=An excellent Czech footballer became a father for the second time: Look at that beautiful baby!|url=https://www.nautiv.com/an-excellent-czech-footballer-became-a-father-for-the-second-time-look-at-that-beautiful-baby/|website=Nautiv|date=11 October 2021|access-date=15 December 2021|archive-date=22 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422111318/https://www.nautiv.com/an-excellent-czech-footballer-became-a-father-for-the-second-time-look-at-that-beautiful-baby/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

